        "contact": {
          "name": "Arul John",
          "url": "https://aruljohn.com"
        },
        "description": "Get your IP Address using this API. This is a free public web service that returns the client's IP address in either text or JSON format.",
        "license": {
          "name": "Free to use",
          "url": "https://aruljohn.com/api/"
        },
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://api.aruljohn.com"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Arul's IP API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Look up the caller's public IP address as plain text or JSON, with no signup or API key",
        "homepage": "https://aruljohn.com/api/",
        "docs_url": "https://aruljohn.com/api/",
        "license_short": "Free to use; please be reasonable with request volume",
        "license_md": "- Free public web service, no authentication or API key required\n- Provider asks callers to be reasonable with curl, jQuery, Postman, Ajax or other API call volume\n- No formal SLA or published rate limit; the operator has previously retired other APIs due to abuse\n- CORS is enabled, so the API can be called directly from browser JavaScript",
        "about_md": "Arul's IP API is a small public web service run by [Arul John](https://aruljohn.com/) that echoes back the caller's public IP address. It is hosted at `api.aruljohn.com` and documented alongside the operator's other public utilities at [aruljohn.com/api](https://aruljohn.com/api/).\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- `GET /ip` returns the client IP as plain text (for example `199.199.199.199`)\n- `GET /ip/json` returns the same value wrapped in JSON, e.g. `{\"ip\":\"199.199.199.199\"}`\n\nNo authentication, API key, or sign-up is required. CORS is enabled so the endpoints are usable directly from browser JavaScript. There is no published rate limit, but the operator asks callers to be reasonable with request volume.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "ip_address": "The caller's public IP address as plain text, returned by `GET /ip`.",
          "ipn": "The caller's public IP address wrapped in a JSON object, returned by `GET /ip/json`."
        },
